This paper deals with designing efficient channel access schemes for wireless communications, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed algorithm is based on the theory of multiarmed bandits (MAB), which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the algorithm involves tuning control parameters to achieve optimal performance, which is a characteristic of control systems (cs.SY). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.IT and cs.NI, followed by cs.LG, cs.SY, and cs.AI.
